  "lastUpdatedOn": "2013-02-04",
  "religion": "Sarah Brightman is a devout Catholic.",
  "politicalViews": "She's non-political, but did manage to outbid the U.S. government for a trip to the International Space Station.",
  "author": "Caitlin Frye",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 1
    },
    {
      "parentId": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Sarah Brightman was born and raised in Berkhamsted, Hertfordshire, England."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 2
    },
    {
      "parentId": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "I expected to find more on Brightman's Catholic faith, but I could only find one quote which clearly shows her devotion to her religion."
    },
    {
      "parentId": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Talking about her Christmas album, "
    },
    {
      "parentId": 2,
      "type": "emphasis",
      "text": "A Winter Symphony"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "text": ", which features songs heavy on religion like \"Silent Night,\" \"Ave Maria,\" and \"In the Bleak Midwinter,\" Brightman said,"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 3
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 4,
      "parentId": 3
    },
    {
      "parentId": 4,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "My family is Catholic, and my mother is very Catholic. The whole Christian side of Christmas has been an important thing in my family. Christmas is actually a very textured moment of the year for me.",
      "sourceTitle": "12/21: Sarah Brightman at Jobing.com Arena.",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.azcentral.com/ent/music/articles/2008/12/11/20081211brightman.html"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 5
    },
    {
      "parentId": 5,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Her holiday album isn't the only one with religious songs either. Just looking at titles, she has songs like \""
    },
    {
      "parentId": 5,
      "type": "link",
      "text": "Heaven is Here",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.sing365.com/music/lyric.nsf/Heaven-is-Here-lyrics-Sarah-Brightman/4D09B0DD28B61E954825696100133C58"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 5,
      "type": "text",
      "text": ",\" \""
    },
    {
      "parentId": 5,
      "type": "link",
      "text": "How Can Heaven Love Me?",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.metrolyrics.com/how-can-heaven-love-me-lyrics-sarah-brightman.html"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 5,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "\" and \""
    },
    {
      "parentId": 5,
      "type": "link",
      "text": "Angel",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.lyricsreg.com/lyrics/sarah+brightman/Angel/"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 5,
      "type": "text",
      "text": ".\" And one of her albums is called "
    },
    {
      "parentId": 5,
      "type": "emphasis",
      "text": "Eden"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 5,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 6
    },
    {
      "parentId": 6,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Maybe she doesn't like to talk about her faith much, maybe people don't ask her very often, or maybe I just couldn't find those interviews. But regardless, she's made it pretty clear that she's a religious Catholic.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": 7
    },
    {
      "parentId": 7,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Take that, NASA"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 8
    },
    {
      "parentId": 8,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "The only even remotely political thing that Sarah Brightman has done is try to go to space, or at least pay for a ticket. Brightman outbid NASA–or in other words, the U.S. government–for a spot on a trip up the International Space Station. She reportedly spent more than $50 million for the ticket",
      "sourceTitle": "Space Tourist Sarah Brightman Buys Seat on Russian Soyuz Spacecraft.",
      "sourceUrl": "http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/space-tourist-sarah-brightman-buys-seat-russian-soyuz/story?id=17384120"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 8,
      "type": "text",
      "text": " and will spend six month training in Russia for the mission.",
      "sourceTitle": "Sarah Brightman books flight to space station.",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.guardian.co.uk/science/2012/oct/11/sarah-brightman-space-station"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 8,
      "type": "text",
      "text": " But hey, if you've got more money to spare than the United States, then why not? She said,"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 9
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 10,
      "parentId": 9
    },
    {
      "parentId": 10,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "I think it will be a beautiful journey and I think just to look back at our planet from that perspective is life changing, it has to be.",
      "sourceTitle": "Sarah Brightman: my space flight will be 'life-changing.'",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WoGe-9gGMdM"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 11
    },
    {
      "parentId": 11,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "It's hardly partisan politics, but it's something all right. In fact, she doesn't appear to have anything to say about the partisan in her country or anywhere else. I guess she's just sticking to peaceful international missions for now. If you know anything else, please give us a holler in the comments!"
    }
  ],
